video.title: Life with Boys
video.synopsis: This sitcom follows the crazy life of teenager Tess Foster as she grapples with being the only girl in an all-male household.

episodes.synopsis: Tess wants to go on a date to prove to her nemesis, Kaylee, that she can be a wrestler and still be attractive to boys, but discovers that might not be the right reason to do it.
episodes.title: Misguided Motives with Boys

episodes.synopsis: Tess, frustrated with her brothers' lack of manners and hygiene, calls in Grandma (a.k.a.the Big Gun) to come teach them a lesson but ends up getting one in return.
episodes.title: A Perfect Life with Boys

episodes.synopsis: Tess is forced to join the Mathlete Team at school and it puts her social reputation in jeopardy.
episodes.title: Social Death with Boys

episodes.synopsis: With the Foster family officially too big to share one bathroom, Tess and the boys agree to pick up the slack around the house and Jack takes a second job.
episodes.title: Bathroom Battles with Boys

episodes.synopsis: When Tess learns that Jack is struggling to cope with his kids growing up, she has a hard time telling him the truth about wanting to have a more mature fifteenth birthday.
episodes.title: Birthdays with Boys

episodes.synopsis: When Tess catches Sam smoking in an attempt to roll with a cooler crowd, she calls a secret sibling meeting to intervene.
episodes.title: Smokin' with Boys

episodes.synopsis: A school trip to Italy looks like it will be a disaster when Tess gets roomed with Kaylee, forcing Tess to figure out a way around Kaylee's pestering ways.
episodes.title: Blah, Blah, Blah with Boys

episodes.synopsis: Tess breaks her promise to Jack that she wouldn't get her ears pierced until she was fifteen but before she can tell him the truth, he gives her permission... but can she go to a party knowing she lied to get there?
episodes.title: This Time the Problem Is with Dad and Not with Boys

episodes.synopsis: Tess and her brothers find their Christmas plans wrecked when Jack announces that he wants them all to surprise Grandma for Christmas.
episodes.title: Chrisbus with Boys

episodes.synopsis: Tess has to wrestle against last year's City Champion, Bobby Parelli, and accidentally lets their impromptu pre-match competition go a little too far.
episodes.title: Disarmed with Boys

episodes.synopsis: Tess discovers that her best friend, Allie, has started dating her wrestling nemesis, Bobby Parelli.
episodes.title: Trouble with Boys

episodes.synopsis: Tess has a hard time telling Allie that she's still seeing Bobby, and a surprise visit from Emily Osment (Hannah Montana) only complicates matters.
episodes.title: Double Trouble with Boys

episodes.synopsis: Tess gets caught up in a web of white lies, which almost causes her to lose both her boyfriend and her best friend.
episodes.title: When Something Better Comes Along with Boys

episodes.synopsis: In the wake of her break-up with Bobby, Tess takes some time off from dating, which suddenly makes her irresistible to every boy in school.
episodes.title: Hitting the Breaks with Boys

episodes.synopsis: Tess decides to set Jack up on a date by creating a fake online-dating profile for him, with Allie's help.
episodes.title: Set Up's with Boys

episodes.synopsis: After Tess and Allie accidentally embarrass Sam, Allie agrees to pretend they are dating to help rebuild his damaged reputation.
episodes.title: The Big Kiss Off with Boys

episodes.synopsis: Worried that their friendship might start drifting apart, Tess and Allie try to share each other's interests and instead, end up in the Principal's Office.
episodes.title: In the Principal's Office with Boys

episodes.synopsis: When Tess finds out Sam was only invited to a party to be made fun of, she goes to great lengths to spare his feelings.
episodes.title: Monkey Talk with Boys

episodes.synopsis: Tess convinces Jack to let her join the wrestling team, but then discovers that she may have damaged her "girl-cred" in the process.
episodes.title: Wrestling with Boys

episodes.synopsis: When a fashion guru comes to Westfield, Tess tries to impress him by creating a contest-winning design that will get her all the way to New York.
episodes.title: Fashion Faux Pas with Boys

episodes.synopsis: Tess tries getting along with Kaylee after Jack starts dating her mom, but when it proves impossible, she claims nightmares are telling her they shouldn't be together.
episodes.title: Nightmares with Boys

episodes.synopsis: Tess and Sam are driving each other crazy at school, so when Tess gets a wrestling scholarship offer from Pineview Prep, she takes it.
episodes.title: Driven Crazy with Boys

episodes.synopsis: When a frustrated Tess wishes she were a boy, a witch grants her request. But Tess learns that being a boy isn't as easy as it looks.
episodes.title: Episode 1

episodes.synopsis: When Tess's ultimate Christmas gift for her dad -- family harmony -- instead leads to family fighting, Spencer runs away from home.
episodes.title: Episode 2

episodes.synopsis: Tess tries to juggle an all girls night and a date with a cute boy only to discover that trying to make everyone happy usually makes her miserable.
episodes.title: Episode 3

episodes.synopsis: To help land her dad the job of vice principal in charge of stricter discipline, Tess and Allie turn their school into a "problem school."
episodes.title: Episode 4

episodes.synopsis: Tess convinces the school district to replace the aging wrestling mats only to discover that she should be careful about what she wishes for.
episodes.title: Episode 5

episodes.synopsis: When Jack drives Gabe and Sam to a concert, Tess tries to manage babysitting Spencer while having a girls night with Allie.
episodes.title: Episode 6

episodes.synopsis: Turning matchmaker, Tess tries to get her popular older brother, Gabe, to date a girl he wouldn't normally ask out.
episodes.title: Episode 7

episodes.synopsis: When Tess is hired as a dog-washer, she discovers that the job isn't as easy as it sounds.
episodes.title: Episode 8

episodes.synopsis: Tess dates a boy who makes bets with his friends about what he can get her to do, while Spencer loses the school rat in the house.
episodes.title: Episode 9

episodes.synopsis: When Tess and Sam earn their driver's licenses, all the siblings have to share dad's car, which turns into big problems when Allie needs Tess's help.
episodes.title: Episode 10

episodes.synopsis: When Tess causes Sam's new friend Adam to develop amnesia, she must fix him before he has to deliver a big speech.
episodes.title: Episode 11

episodes.synopsis: When her dad forces her to show a nerdy new student around school, Tess tries to make him cool to avoid bullying.
episodes.title: Episode 12

episodes.synopsis: When Tess and Gabe enter the same singing contest to win a $200 prize, Tess gets to meet country singing star Brooklyn Roebuck.
episodes.title: Episode 13

episodes.synopsis: When singer Victoria Duffield asks Tess to sing at her concert, the timing conflicts with Tess's need to be by Allie's side during surgery.
episodes.title: Episode 14

episodes.synopsis: Tess steps over the line when she sells her brother Gabe's song to a famous musician without getting his permission first.
episodes.title: Episode 15

episodes.synopsis: In order to pay for a much-coveted second bathroom, Tess convinces her klutzy family to audition for a family dance show competition.
episodes.title: Episode 16

episodes.synopsis: Jack wants to spend spring break with the family, but Tess and her brothers want to spend it with friends, so Tess calls her grandfather for help.
episodes.title: Episode 17

episodes.synopsis: It's final exam week at school, so Tess's dad and her brothers collaborate with Allie to search for a way to calm Tess down.
episodes.title: Episode 18
